The 'Lazy' pattern involves immediately redirecting to the login page when a 401 error is detected, as shown in the following code snippet:

javascript
axios.interceptors.response.use(null, error => {
  if (error.response.status === 401) {
    window.location.href = '/login'; // Loses unsaved data
    return Promise.reject(error);
  }
});


This approach is discouraged because it fails to recover unsaved user input, leading to a poor user experience.
